  "text": "The GCC Internal Compiler Error (ICE) 'verify_gimple failed' is traced through the following components:\n\n1. **GIMPLE Verification Pass**: The main GIMPLE verification functions are implemented in gcc/tree-cfg.cc. The `verify_gimple_in_seq` function (line 5244) is the entry point for verifying a sequence of GIMPLE statements. It calls the internal helper function `verify_gimple_in_seq_2` (line 5160) which iterates through statements and calls `verify_gimple_stmt` (line 5034) to check individual GIMPLE statements.\n\n2. **ICE Trigger Point**: When verification fails and the `ice` parameter is true, `verify_gimple_in_seq` (line 5249 in gcc/tree-cfg.cc) calls `internal_error(\"%<verify_gimple%> failed\")` to report the error. Similarly, `verify_gimple_in_cfg` (line 5443) can also trigger the ICE at line 5599.\n\n3. **ICE Handler**: The `internal_error` function is defined in gcc/diagnostic-global-context.cc (line 776) and is responsible for handling internal consistency check failures. It calls the diagnostic system's `diagnostic_impl` method with kind=`ice` and then calls `gcc_unreachable()` to terminate compilation.\n\n4. **Pass Pipeline Integration**: The GIMPLE verification is integrated into the pass pipeline through gcc/passes.cc (lines 2100-2102) which calls either `verify_gimple_in_cfg` or `verify_gimple_in_seq` conditionally based on whether a CFG has been built. While GIMPLE verification is not scheduled as a separate pass in gcc/passes.def, it is invoked programmatically after optimization passes complete.\n\nThe error flow is: passes.cc -> tree-cfg.cc (verify_gimple_in_seq/verify_gimple_in_cfg) -> verify_gimple_stmt -> diagnostic-global-context.cc (internal_error) -> ICE output."
}

